<item>
            <title>[LU-6495] push Fujitsu IB multi-rail patch to Gerrit</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6495</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Please push the IB multi-rail patch to the Gerrit fs/lustre-release branch.  My understanding is that the patch is currently based on Lustre 2.6.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ideally the patch would be based on the current master branch.  However, if there are a large number of non-trivial conflicts applying the patch to master, it may be necessary to rewind your local branch to 2.7.0 or 2.6.0 (e.g. &quot;git checkout -b 2.6.0&quot;) and pushing the patch there as a starting point.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be possible to use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;git am &amp;lt;patch file&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; to import the Git patch file (which may even apply it to the original commit that it was based on) so that the original author (NAGUCHI Yoshinori &amp;lt;y-naguchi@jp.fujitsu.com&amp;gt;) is preserved.  If not, then the patch could be applied with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;git apply --author=&quot;NAGUCHI Yoshinori &amp;lt;y-naguchi@jp.fujitsu.com&amp;gt;&quot; &amp;lt;patch file&amp;gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
